@xumingming , currently DSL/SQL modules use parent version `0.7.0-SNAPSHOT`, while in `pom.xml` of SQL we declare as `0.6.0` explicitly.

As I know, no other modules use code of SQL part,(_correct me here if anything I miss_). You may follow the two steps to sync-up with latest main branch:
1. upgrade DSL/SQL module with parent version `2.1.0-SNAOSHOT`, and specify Beam libraries `2.0.0` in SQL   `pom.xml`; --There may be some code change to do the upgrade
2. then rebase from beam/master branch;

@jkff , I have added the unit testing for which I used an embedded source used in the link  https://github.com/apache/hive/blob/master/hcatalog/core/src/test/java/org/apache/hive/hcatalog/data/TestReaderWriter.java suggested by @iemejia .

I used SourceTestUtils for source related part and end-to-end testing for overall read & write scenarios.

Looking forward to your review & comments !
